Inoa |date=April 15, 2019 |publisher=honolulu.gov |accessdate=December 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.staradvertiser.com/2019/04/18/hawaii-news/newswatch/honolulu-rail-transit-authority-seeks-feedback-on-hawaiian-names-for-train-stations/ |title=Honolulu rail transit authority seeks feedback on Hawaiian names for train stations |author=Wu, Nina |date=April 18, 2019 |newspaper=Honolulu Star-Advertiser |accessdate=May 29, 2019}}</ref> The proposed name for this station, '''Makalapa''', means \"ridge face\" or \"ridge front\" and refers to an ancient crater above the H\u0101lawa flats.<ref name=HSNP-2>{{cite web |url=http://hartdocs.honolulu.gov/docushare/dsweb/Get/Document-22717/HSN-Program-Overview-2019.pdf |title=Hawaiian Station Naming Program |date=March 2019 |publisher=Honolulu Authority for Rapid Transportation |accessdate=19 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web |url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/honolulurail/albums/72157688108143663 |title=Pearl Harbor |author=Honolulu Transit |website=flickr.com}}\n\n[[Category:Honolulu Rail Transit stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations scheduled to open in 2022]]\n\n{{Hawaii-railstation-stub}}\n{{Honolulu-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n  | style=\n  | name=Makalapa<br/><small>(Pearl Harbor Naval Base)</small>\n  | type= Future [[Honolulu Rail Transit|HART]] [[rapid transit]] station\n  | image=\n  | image_size=\n  | image_caption=\n  | address=\n  | coordinates={{coord |21.353555|-157.935703|display=inline,title |format=dms}}\n  | line={{Rail color box|system=Honolulu Rail Transit|line=HART}}\n  | other= {{bus icon|12px|Intercity Bus}} '''[[TheBus (Honolulu)|TheBus]]''': TBD\n  | platform=2 [[side platform]]s\n  | depth=\n  | levels=2\n  | tracks=2\n  | parking=No\n  | bicycle=\n  | baggage_check=\n  | opening= 2022 (planned)<ref name=NaInoa-2/>\n  | closed=\n  | rebuilt=\n  | ADA=Yes\n  | code=\n  | owned=[[Honolulu Rail Transit]]\n  | zone=\