 Trail Road.\n |-\n | [[Camp Saukenauk]] || Mississippi Valley Council || Mendon || [http://www.mississippivalleybsa.org/Camping/SSR Active] || \n |-\n | [[Camp Tawasentha]] ||  || Viola, IL ||  || <!-- found ref to 1936 patch -->\n |-\n | [[Camp Vandeventer]] || Greater St. Louis Area Council || Waterloo, IL || [https://stlbsa.org/activities/camping/camp-properties/camp-vandeventer/ Active] || \n |-\n | [[Camp Warren Levis]] || Greater St. Louis Area Council || Godfrey, IL || [https://stlbsa.org/activities/camping/camp-properties/camp-warren-levis/ Active] || \n |-\n | [[Camp Wokanda]] ||  W.D. Boyce Area Council || Peoria, IL  || Closed || Closed in the 1990s; now operated by the City of Peoria, IL.\n |-\n |[https://www.canyoncampbsa.org '''Canyon Camp''']|| Blackhawk Area Council || Stockton, IL ||[https://www.canyoncampbsa.org Active]|| Located near historic Galena, IL\n |-\n | [[Corn Belt Council Boy Scout Reservation]] ||  ||  ||  ||\n |-\n | [[Fellheimer Scout Reservation]] || Prairie Council || Gilson IL || Sold || Owned by a Seventh-day Adventist group; renamed Camp Akita.  [http://www.campakita.com/Camp_Akita_Adventist_Retreat_Center/Home.html ref]\n |-\n | [[Fort Dearborn Scout Camp]] ||  || Park Ridge, IL || Closed || Part of forest preserve\n |-\n | [[H. Earl Hoover Scout Reservation]] ||  || Yorkville, IL ||  || [http://contentdm.unl.edu/cdm/ref/collection/classmod/id/21129 ref]{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n |-\n | [[Ingersoll Scout Reservation]] || W. D. Boyce Council || London Mills, IL || [http://isrsummercamp.org/ Active] || \n |-\n | [[Loud Thunder Scout Reservation]] || Illowa Council || Illinois City, IL ||[https://loudthunder.org/ Active]||\n |-\n | [[Namekagon Scout Reservation]] || Northwest Suburban Council ||  || Sold  || Sold in 1977<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heartwoodconferencecenter.com/history|title=Heartwood Conference Center & Retreat \u2013 Heartwood's History- Trego, WI|website=www.heartwoodconferencecenter.com}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Pine Ridge Scout Reservation]] || Greater St. Louis Area Council || Makanda || [http://stlbsa.org/activities/camping/camp-properties/pine-ridge-scout-camp/ Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Rainbow Council Scout Reservation]] || Rainbow Council || Morris, IL || [http://rsrcamp.wix.com/rsrsummercamp Active] ||\n |-\n | [[Rhodes-France Scout Reservation]] || Lincoln Trails Council || Pana || [http://www.lincolntrailscouncil.org/rfsr.html Active] || \n |-\n | [[Tomo Chi-Chi Knolls]] || Formerly West Suburban Council ||  Gilberts, IL  || Sold || Sold to Kane County Forest Preserve District in 2006.\n|}\n\n=== Indiana ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Indiana}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Big Island Camp]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Buffalo Trace Council Camps]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Louis Ernst]] || Hoosier Trails Council ||Dupont, IN || [https://web.archive.org/web/20161011061146/http://www.hoosiertrailsbsa.org/program-resources/camps-outdoor-programs/camp-louis-ernst/47082 Active] || Primitive camping only \n |-\n | [[Camp Arthur]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Bear Creek]] || Crossroads of America Council || Connersville, IN || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Belzer]] || Crossroads of America Council || Indianapolis, IN  || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Bradford]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Buffalo]] || Sagamore Council || Monticello, IN  || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Carnes]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Chief Little Turtle]] || Anthony Wayne Area Council || Ashley, IN || Active ||\n |- |\n | [[Camp Kikthawenund]] || Crossroads of America Council || Frankton, IN || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Krietenstein]] || Crossroads of America Council || Center Point, IN  || A