ill Active] || \n |-\n | [[Mortimer L. Schiff Scout Reservation]] || Boy Scouts of America || Mendham, New Jersey || Closed || This was a major Boy Scout training facility for almost 50 years.  It was closed in 1979.  It was the location of the first [[Wood Badge (Boy Scouts of America)|Wood Badge]] courses held in the United States.\n |-\n | [[Winnebago Scout Reservation]] ||Patriots' Path Council ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Wood Lake Scout Reservation]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Yards Creek Scout Reservation]] ||  ||  ||Closed || \n|}\n\n=== New Mexico ===\n{{Details|Scouting in New Mexico}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Black Range Cavalcade]] || [[Yucca Council]] || Winston, NM || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Dale Resler]] || [[Yucca Council]] || Cloudcroft, NM || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Gorham Scout Ranch]] || [[Great Southwest Council]] || Albuquerque, NM || Active || Formerly known as Camp Frank Rand. \n |-\n | [[Camp Kidd (New Mexico)|Camp Kidd]] || ||  || Closed ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Tres Ritos]] || [[South Plains Council]] || Vadito, NM || Active ||\n |-\n | [[Dowling Aquatic Base]] || [[Conquistador Council]] || Carlsbad, NM || Active || Situated on the Pecos River.\n |-\n | [[Philmont Scout Ranch]] || [[Boy Scouts of America National Council]] || Cimarron, NM ||  Active ||\n |-\n | [[Wehinahpay Mountain Camp]] || [[Conquistador Council]] || Sacramento, NM || Active ||\n|}\n\n=== New York ===\n{{Details|Scouting in New York}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsor