irwin, KS || Active || Also known as Camp Hansen.\n |-\n |[http://www.jayhawkcouncil.org/ Falley Scout Reservation]|| Jayhawk Area Council || Oskaloosa, KS || Active|| Available to both boy and girl units.\n |-\n | [[Quivira Scout Ranch]] || Quivira Council || Sedan, KS ||Active ||\n|}\n\n=== Kentucky ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Kentucky}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n |-\n | [[Camp Cherokee (Kentucky)|Camp Cherokee]] || Tri-State Area Council || Louisa, KY || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Covered Bridge]] || Formerly Old Kentucky Home Council || Oldham County, KY || Closed || Land has been developed into housing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ringbrothershistory.com/alsprojects/Waggener/St.%20Matthews%20activities/Scouting/Scouting%20At%20Camp%20Coverd%20Bridge.pdf|website=Ring Brothers History|title=Scouting at Camp Covered Bridge|accessdate=20 July 2019}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Crooked Creek]] || Lincoln Heritage Council || Shepherdsville, KY || Active || Also known as the Harry S. Frazier, Jr. Scout Reservation.\n |-\n | [[Camp Roy C. Manchester]] || Lincoln Heritage Council || Benton, KY || Active || \n |-\n | [[Mammoth Cave Council Camp]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[McKee Scout Reservation]] || Blue Grass Council || Jeffersonville, KY || Active || Located within [[Daniel Boone National Forest]].\n |-\n | [[Wildcat Hollow Scout Camp]] || Lincoln Heritage Council || Owensboro, Ky || Active||\n|}\n\n=== Louisiana ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Louisiana}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  