and|Chesapeake Beach]], MD  || Closed || The camp was about 8 miles south of Chesapeake Beach. It was sold in the late 1970s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shorpy.com/node/5151?size=_original |title=Shorpy Historical Photo Archive :: Group Shot: 1925 |publisher=Shorpy.com |date=1925-07-09 |accessdate=2014-01-21}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Tockwogh]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Winona]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Deep Run (Boy Scout camp)|Deep Run]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Horseshoe Scout Reservation]]<ref group=note name= \"Horseshoe\">Horseshoe Scout Reservation is located in both Pennsylvania and Maryland.</ref> || [[Chester County Council]] || || Active [http://www.cccbsa.org/boy-scout-camp-horseshoe]|| Located on the Mason\u2013Dixon line separating Pennsylvania and Maryland.  It is divided into two camps: Camp Horseshoe, in Rising Sun, Maryland, and Camp John H. Ware, III, in Fulton Township, Lancaster County, Pennsylvania.\n |-\n | [[Lillie-Aaron Straus Explorer Base]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Potomac Council Summer Camp]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Rodney Scout Reservation]] || [[Del-Mar-Va Council]] || || Active || 900 acres located at the head of the Chesapeake Bay. It has been in continuous operation since 1923.\n |-\n|}\n\n=== Massachusetts ===\n{{Details|Scouting in Massachusetts}}\n {| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%\" | Camp name\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Council\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"15%\" | Location\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"10%\" | Status\n ! scope=\"col\" width=\"25%\"  class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|Adams Pond Scout Reservation\n|Boston Council\n|[[Barnstead, New Hampshire|Barnstead, NH]]\n|Merged\n|Now T.L. Storer Scout Reservation\n|-\n | Camp Buxton || Narragansett Council ||[[Rehoboth, Massachusetts|Rehoboth, MA]]|| Active ||\n |-\n | [[Cachalot Scout Reservation]] || Narragansett Council ||[[Plymouth, Massachusetts|Plymouth, MA]]|| Active || Located in the [[Myles Standish