ve.org/web/20071121231928/http://mac-bsa.org:80/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=95&Itemid=80|url-status=dead|archive-date=November 21, 2007|title=Mid-America Council, BSA \u2013 Camp Butterfield|date=November 21, 2007}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Cedars]] || Mid-America Council || Near Cedar Bluffs, NE || Active || 1939\u2013Present. Camp Cedars comprises the western half of the Covered Wagon Scout Reservation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mac-bsa.org/camp_info.aspx?ID=2|title=Camp Cedars}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Cornhusker]] || Cornhusker Council || Near Du Bois, NE || Active || 1956\u2013Present. South of Humboldt, NE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cornhuskercouncil.org/camping/camp-cornhusker/camp-cornhusker.html|title=Cornhusker Council, BSA : Camping : Camp Cornhusker : Camp Cornhusker|website=www.cornhuskercouncil.org}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Eagle]] || Mid-America Council || Near Cedar Bluffs, NE || Active || 1963\u2013Present. Camp Eagle comprises the eastern half of the Covered Wagon Scout Reservation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mac-bsa.org/camp_info.aspx?ID=3|title=Camp Eagle}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Kitaki]] ||  ||  || ||\n |-\n | [[Camp Opal Springs]] || Tri-Trails Council (defunct) || Near Wellfleet, NE || Closed || Site was occupied by Dancing Leaf Earth Lodge until 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omaha.com/news/nebraska/the-good-life-after-years-wellfleet-s-prehistoric-hilton-ends/article_00ecc45c-4d7e-5a73-97be-4636f4e2eea9.html|title=The Good Life: After 30 years, Wellfleet's 'prehistoric Hilton' ends run as must-see earth lodge|first=Paul Hammel / The Good|last=Life|website=Omaha.com}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Camp Wa-kon-da]] || Mid-America Council || Bellevue, NE || Active || Camp Wa-kon-da is in Bellevue, Nebraska and covers 40 acres of wooded bluffs, adjacent to Fontenelle Forest<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mac-bsa.org/camp_info.aspx?ID=6|title=Camp Wa-kon-da}}</ref>\n |-\n | [[Little Sioux Scout Reservation]] || Mid-America Council || Near L